summary: This is an email chain between FBI agents discussing the status of seized digital evidence in the Epstein case. It details the quantity of computers, phones, hard drives, and other media seized, and notes that approximately 20 computers still need to be processed.

events.title: FBI Email on Seized Evidence
events.description: FBI agents correspond about the inventory of digital evidence seized in the Epstein case, including computers, phones, hard drives, and other media.

keyFacts: The FBI seized approximately 35-40 computers, 11 phones/iPads, 21 hard drives, 4 recorders, and hundreds of DVD/CDROMs in the Epstein case.
As of May 6, 2020, approximately 20 computers from the seizure still needed to be processed.
The communication is an internal FBI email chain discussing evidence inventory and processing status.
